headline: OpenTable Launches All-in-One Marketplace for Private and Group Dining
summary: OpenTable, a global leader in restaurant tech, today announced the launch of its new all-in-one marketplace for private and group dining. The product replaces scattered searches, calls, and emails with one reliable hub – making it easier for diners to plan large gatherings and for restaurants to drive revenue with less friction.

headline: What Does the Ryanair Settlement Mean for Booking Holdings Shares in 2025?
summary: If you are sitting on the fence about Booking Holdings stock, you are in good company. Over the past year, this travel industry heavyweight has soared by 40.7%, boosting long-term investors with a five-year gain north of 240%. Year-to-date, the stock has added another 12.9% even as the market digests fresh legal headlines and shifting risk perceptions. Most recently, the slight 0.2% dip over the last week seems more like a pause than a red flag, and the 1.9% rise in the past month supports...
